Djokovic Advances at French Open as Hanescu Quits With Injury in Third Set

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-05-25T16:14:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/djokovic-advances-at-french-open-as-hanescu-quits-with-injury-in-third-set.html
Second-seed Novak Djokovic advanced
to the third round of the  French Open  after his opponent,
Romanian Victor Hanescu, quit in the third set.  The Serb was winning 6-4, 6-1, 2-3 when Hansecu retired
with a thigh injury. The victory sets up a meeting with
 Argentina ’s Juan Martin del Potro, and extends Djokovic’s
winning streak to 39 straight to start the year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  